# Discussions Module Rules

## Discussion Entity

Public comments under request or proposal.

## Discussion Fields

- `id` - Unique identifier
- `requestId` - Request ID (foreign key to Request, optional)
- `proposalId` - Proposal ID (foreign key to Proposal, optional)
- `userId` - ID of user who left comment (foreign key to User)
- `replyToId` - ID of comment being replied to (foreign key to Discussion, optional)
- `content` - Comment text
- `createdAt` - Creation date
- `updatedAt` - Update date

## Discussion Endpoints

- `GET /api/requests/:id/discussions` - Get discussions for request
- `GET /api/proposals/:id/comments` - Get comments for proposal
- `POST /api/requests/:id/discussions` - Add comment to request
- `POST /api/proposals/:id/comments` - Add comment to proposal
- `PATCH /api/discussions/:id` - Update comment (author only)
- `DELETE /api/discussions/:id` - Delete comment (author only)

## Discussion Service

- Create public comments
- Support nested replies (reply to comment)
- Update and delete comments
- Get discussions with nested structure
- Filter by request or proposal

## Business Logic

1. **Creating comment:**
   - Save comment to database
   - Link to request or proposal
   - Support replies to other comments

2. **Nested structure:**
   - Comments can be top-level or replies
   - Build tree structure when fetching
   - Show reply count

## Validation

- Content: required, min 1 character, max 2000 characters
- Must be linked to either request or proposal
- Can reply to existing comment
